Basic import syntax:
from module import first a f, second, third as t

Importing modules from your filesystem:
import sys
sys.path.append('/path/to/directory_containing_your_module')
import mymodule

PEP conventions for import formatting
1. std library imports
2. third party library imports
3. local imports

Packages:
- directory
|-- __init__.py  # this makes the directory a package!
|-- file1.py     # I believe this is considiered a module
|-- file2.py

When you import a module, the init script will be run
